content.text: Trial 2/5, Stage 'ytraverse2': Please describe the image and compute the stiffness matrix.

The image shows a groove with a rectangular shape on a screen, highlighted by a red circle on its right side. The groove appears to be oriented in a way that suggests aligning with the camera's Y-axis (depth) and Z-axis (upward), while the X-axis runs perpendicular to the screen's plane.

Given this orientation, we can set up a stiffness matrix with higher stiffness along the groove direction (aligned with X-axis in the local groove frame) and lower stiffness perpendicular to it.

### Stiffness Matrix

  "stiffness_matrix": [
    [100, 0, 0],
    [0, 250, 0],
    [0, 0, 250]
  ]
